WinRAR is a shareware file archiver and data compression utility developed by Eugene Roshal and distributed by Alexander Roshal,[3] first released in autumn of 1993.[4] It is one of the few applications that is able to create RAR archives natively, because the encoding method is held to be proprietary. Command-line versions, simply called "RAR", exist for Mac OS X, Linux, and FreeBSD.
